DLW-SPUN · the full weave of Francesca da Rimini

who   : A noblewoman who loved Paolo, her husband's brother.
what  : Blown forever on the black wind with the carnal, never parted from him.
where : Circle II — Lust (Minos judges at the gate).
why   : 'Love led us to one death' — a kiss, and the book that was their go-between.
when  : For one moment's surrender, and forever after.
how   : She tells it so gently that the pilgrim faints for pity.

class : Circle II · Lust · swept on the black wind
